Jay Berzofsky, a professor at the American National Cancer Institute (Bethesda, Maryland), said: “Our results suggest that we have a very promising vaccine.”
HER2 “stimulates the growth of multiple cancers,” including breast, ovarian, lung and rectum cancer, Professor Berzofsky explained.
A similar method based on highlighting immune cells and “teaching” how to attack cancer cells has been used successfully in the treatment of a type of leukaemia.
